oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real Photo postcard of Hunter Inman and Jess G. Locke
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph shows two men standing in civilian clothing and two soldiers seated. The man standing on the left is Hunter Inman; the soldier seated on the right is Pvt. Jesse G. Locke, 156 Depot Brig. and later of the HQ Co., 317 FA Btry., 81st Div. All of the men are believed to be from the Leiper's Fork area of Williamson County, Tennessee. The unidentified soldier seated on the left wears a medal presented to returning veterans by the citizens of Nashville [see als GWfran001].
